<span style="font-weight: 400;">Clinical depression is an invisible invader of oneâ€™s self. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">It is a serious mental illness and manifests as:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> feelings of utter sadness accompanied with bouts of sudden crying </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">hopelessness, </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">loss of interest, anger, guilt</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">frustration, </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">even irritability (especially in adolescents) </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Physical and mental fatigue</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">disruptions in the normal sleep patterns</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">feelings of anxiety</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">numbed feelings</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Loss of confidence &amp; self-esteem</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Changes in overall weight and in appetite</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Lack of libido</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Unexplained aches and pains</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Impaired thinking and concentration powers</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thinking of suicide</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Doing self-harm</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">These symptoms can last for weeks or months or years and interfere with daily life. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The symptoms are not visible and unless the sufferer voices their pain, their malaise could go unnoticed and untreated for a long time. </span>

