</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â </span><b>Causes of Depression</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Depression is a complicated illness and its causes are not completely understood. From the studied cases and diagnosed, some of the factors that could lead to depression are:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Traumatic situations caused by a deep loss or intense stress. This also includes postnatal depression experienced by some women after the birth of their child.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Illnesses such as bipolar disorder</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Genetics or psychological factors dating back to childhood</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Long standing and/or life-threatening illnesses </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Children can be affected due to the adverse conditions at home(parental disputes) or school (being bullied or peer pressure)</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seasonal Affective Disorder (SAD) - caused by the low light in winter</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sometimes, there is no cause at all but the symptoms appear and create havoc</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Treating Depression</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Treating depression goes a long way in improving the quality of life. Depending on the severity of the depression, it can be treated through drugs and or through alternative therapies known as Talking Therapies.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>Some self-care method of controlling the severity of depression include:</b><b>
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>Exercise: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Regular physical exercise releases endorphins, the feel-good hormones and this can improve the mood.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>Diet: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">A healthy diet rich in vitamins and minerals can help. Avoid drinks, drugs and caffeine as they make the depression worse.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>Building bonds:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Developing and strengthening relationships with family and friends help in keeping depression at bay.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>Remaining stress-free:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Following a daily routine that promotes overall wellbeing and reduces stress is important in preventing and even managing depression.</span>

